\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was it her parents stall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, they were business people were {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Harrisons{\*\xmlclose}
. But they always got the name of Cockell, the older people know them you know. And - they always got - Cockell because they fetched cockle into Keighley market, that Gilbert Wilsnon's stall that was in the market, fish stall, well that
 was me grandfather {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Harrison{\*\xmlclose}'s - stall. Now - their mother - was an {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Harrison{\*\xmlclose}
. She was my mother's aunt and she were my great-aunt, you know, and - she was sister - you know, to me - me grandfather - to me grandfather, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So she was in service and she helped on the family stall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Once she got married did she do any work after that or was she just a housewife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She was for a while but my mother could never sit down. She went and worked for - a - what they call its, Earnshaws, th
e laundry. She was lovely, she could do some - she was their - ironer, she used to do all the ironing and - and the lot, she - well she - she - she did all the ironing - and everything, and then when they gave up - before she died, about three - four - fo
u
r - she'd be about four or five year before she died, she used to go to - oh before that she - she used to help me cousin Edna, she used to go and - do the - do all the bedding for him at the - baths, from the laundry, from the - lodging house, she used t
o
 wash - oh they were beautiful beds you know, he had 'em beautiful, and she used to go there. And she were up to him you know, and he - he thought there were nothing like her, you know, and then he married someone that had been a servant from Carlisle and
 they did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So she became something of a laundress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she could do anything my mother. Could wait at table, lay the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she go back to work when you were quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, I don't remember her but she didn't - I don't - she -
 she work - worked at the laundry a lit - a little while but she - she - she - I don't remember her doing any work, I never remember me mother - going out, she never worked in the mill. Or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But doing this laundry work, was that while you were a little girl or as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh when I was a little girl you know, because I - she used to go and - then when me dad left her she went back to - the laundry you know. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 That was when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So for some years she was just a housewife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was it part time work or full time that she was doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh it were full time work. But sometime - if she were off a day - she were - had something else on - they used to say when she was o
ff it was like three people being off. She - never stopped, she - never stopped for her meals, she - she finished the job before she gave up. She were like that. Well I'm like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you were a little girl and she was doing this laundry work who looked after you while she was out at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh she never left me when I was - helpless. She never left me when I - I couldn't look after meself. Grown up, I were grown up, I were - you know - well - after I were fourteen you know. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I should like to ask you about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You seem to have spent most of your childhood at the house on Rosemount Terrace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many rooms were there in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
The room - there were a room and - I didn't know, there were two bedrooms, attic, I don't know, you know, I've forgot that. But - then - when - when I - when I - come back to - from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose}, I went 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose} you know - I went with my - youngest boy was six month old and I was there about ten year. And - and then - I - I - I - I took a little shop. In - in my name, on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Thornton Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} there, just at the end, you know, near Cab, and - my husband was a big ganger. Yes. He were - he - he used to 
- be taking pounds out of the drawer and I worked, I went to - to the mill I worked in Bradford and he - of course he were - and I used to let him look after the shop, but he used to take pounds, and he'd go and he'd - back horses. Now he were very lucky.
 And if he - he - had a good win, he'd - take the children and he'd buy 'em all kinds of things, to wear, but he never gave 'em a penny. You see, and he - he'd take 'em into a - restaurant, you know - it was that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We'll just get back to this house at Rosemount Terrace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You think there were two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, I - I don't quite remember 'cos I wasn't so old you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How old were you when you left it, about fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, I wasn't fourteen - I was - when we left it I was only about seven or eight. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
So which house do you remember best that you lived in with your parents when you were younger? Which is the house that sticks in your mind best and you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Arcourt Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 were the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We'll talk about the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Arcourt Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well there were two bedrooms there and a house and a - the kitchen, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Four rooms altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was there a cellar or an attic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. No cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did anyone else besides your parents and you live at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You never had any lodgers anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, we never had no lodgers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother pay anyone ever to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. She used to learn me to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh me mother did - took the washing, she took the washing to Keighley baths. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was that the wash house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, there were wash house, just - you know, just - just - you went on Scotch Street and you turned up
 between them - houses you know where the blind house were, and there, and - oh but they've pulled 'em down now you know. Well they used to - she - there used to be a wash house there, it's been given up about - six - six year, oh perhaps a bit more.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And she always took her washing to the wash house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh yes, and she only had one machine and wouldn't have - nobody never got to use it only her. She was such a - clean - washer, and she used to leave everything everything spick and span, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she go to the wash house because she felt it made a mess of the house doing it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well you see she hadn't time because when she did her washing - she used to have to go to work and you see she used to be able to mangle 'em there 'cos the
y had rollers and used to mangle 'em and - and then she'd only to iron - you know, when she'd time to come home. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She was actually working at the wash house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. No, no, she washed her own clothes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother or father mend your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Me mother made all my clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she mend them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, always. We never had no ragged clothes on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you ever have to wear second hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Never. No. I've had do since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But not then, not when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where were they bought when you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh various town - various places in town you know - the - there were - Midgley's and - of course a lot of 'em - given up now, and I used to get me dresses ma
de at a - a lady's up Highfield lane, she used to - make me dresses what - for the better wear you know. And costumes, and - and - what they call its at the end of Skipton Road - what did they call them - Williamsons, it were right big shop but you will r
emember that, they pulled it down, and they built that there shoe shop there, but it was a right high class shop and they used to have furs and all sorts you know, and I used to get me clothes there, she used to have me clothes there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But she also made some dresses for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she always - yes, she made all me summer dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She bought coats and things for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, but - she had them made there you know for better wear, properly tailor made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When did you get new clothes, did you get them every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
I got two - two sets of new clothes every year. Oh yes. I never wore the clothes through the week that I had for Sunday. But when I - I - I'd get a - I - a - I had a - you know, and they was always kept nice, and I - and 
then - when - when I got new clothes, I - I'd have to - wear them that had been for Sunday - weekdays you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you'd get them fairly regularly every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, my mother never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about shoes, did you get those new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I used to get them at \endash  Massey\rquote s on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Bow Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. They used to make shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have to wear clogs for school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Never wore clogs in me life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You always had shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father repair them when they needed repairing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, they was always sent to be repaired to the cobblers. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh - only - only I remember when he were - when - when she was in confinement and - saying he used to bake and do all 
kinds. I - I baked when I were nine year old when my father were laid after the accident and - I - I fetched the - the bowl to the bed and - and - they told me what to do, he did, and I baked half a stone of bread and - and baked ever after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 That was when he'd had his accident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes. While me mother were - out - you know, well she were - then she used to wait on big dinners for the - what they call it, freemasons and that you know. She were - beautiful woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So they told you when she had been confined?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, he used to do - oh yes, he'd - yes, he'd do the jobs dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You don't remember him actually doing these jobs but you were told this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I just have a - a - recollection of him doing things you know for mother when she was poorly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Normally, under normal circumstances he wouldn't do the cleaning or cooking or washing up would he would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Who, me dad? Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about making fires, would he make the fires for her in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh no. My mother used to get up and she used to have my father's - breakfast laid ready for him to put in his mouth. I did - my husband. And - and I used to dress my husband had no clothes when I married him and I bought him - when - and - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Burtons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} had - opened you know, bought him all - a new top coat and - and - and a new trilby and - and been dressed up like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But that was your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, and my mother bought him - a gold watch and chain and - and - a Albert, and then - h
e went and he - he fell by the wayside, my husband, he - he didn't get locked up or anything like that, but he - he went into a public house and he took over me to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose}
. I followed him, yes. And I were having my youngest boy. I never slept with him no 
more. Oh no. Oh no. I'd never do him wrong. Two wrongs don't make a right. But - this - she were a prostitute, and the he went with me, and we saw him, with the woman, and he'd pawned his top coat, it cost me twenty pound to get them out, his top coat and
 that at bottom of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Leeds Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. You know, I don't tell anybody about these things. We all have our faults. Haven't we? But - as for having another man or being - intimate with another man, it never entered my head because I would - I wouldn't allow - I could
 be friends with them, no, and decent but I - I - I wouldn't - hurt no woman. I was hurt very much, but - there's lots of people knew you know and his sister said, well I wouldn't have stopped with him. Well I did, I threatened, and he used to go out only
 at weekend he'd go, never took me out. He used to - I used to be dressed up, sat there, and I - had to be there, the only thing he didn't stop me for was from going to church on a Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He'd stay at home then to look after the boys would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
He wouldn't - because me mother looked after the children. Me mother used to say you're dressing him for other women. But he said, and I know all about this, and I could tell him, he used to say, have you been up the town, has somebody been telling you? A
nd I said, no, they haven't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I'll go back to your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you were a little girl and you were living at Arcourt Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 It would be a rented house I suppose wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember him ever doing any decorating at the house or any repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, me mother did all the decorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother did it did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, I've done it and all, I - I've gone out and done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would your father do any decorating?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I never saw me father do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he do any repairs that were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. I - I don't remember that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Or improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I didn't remember anything like that, they weren't as particular them days as they are now. Well the - the houses
 weren't as badly done to as they - they are now you know. People didn't destroy places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
When you were a little girl do you remember your father helping your mother by dressing you or undressing you or bathing you, anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh me father never touched me, no. Always my mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember him ever reading to you or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, he used to read to me and tell me stories. And I remember him once saying you know - I used to be - always got - I - I were v
ery a - afraid - I - I'd be about eleven, ten or eleven then, I remember getting up out of bed one night, and - and going into - their bedroom you know, and - waking me father up and saying, are - are you frightened to die? And he said, no, said, but it's
 
necessary to love your father God. And serve him all your life, that you may become a channel through which his power can flow. I'll never forget me father saying that. He were right good living man you know, me father. He used to be a - I - I - remember 
them saying used to go hand hand him and me mother the Wesleyan Methodist, and he used to be a local preacher, and my - my oldest son - used to be a local preacher. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he ever take you out without your mother, would he ever take you walks or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh yes, used to take me in the green fields when - I remember when we were in the north you know, we lived - we had to go across - green fields to me grandma, she lived in Cornforth Lane, and - we'd to cover - two - well three green fie
lds and - and when we got - to the other side we'd to go up another long lane before we come to me grannie's you know, and he used to take me every Sunday for walks you know after Sunday school, I used to go to Sunday school and I used to have a dress - y
ou know, every Easter, I used to be - have a - special dress for Easter Sunday. Used to get prizes you know at Sunday school then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember your father ever looking after you when your mother had to go out for some reason?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh never. My mother never left me when I was - not old enough to look after myself. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I had to, my mother learnt me - to - when I got old enough to - to -
 wash the floor and - and I used to wash up, I had to wash up and had brasses cleaning or - them days they had brass fire irons and - all kinds of brass things and I used to say to my mother - you want to put them in the cupboard and - she said, never min
d putting them in the cupboard, get 'em cleaned. Yes. And she used to say - and - and what she - had to - do the corners, never mind the middle, do the corners, people can see - yes. I used to do it all, well for myself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How long did you have to do these little jobs, as long as you lived at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh - oh all the time I lived at home I had to do my share. My mother - worked hard you know and she was a good mother and - and it was to my good that she did because I - I thank her every day of 
my life. Because I learnt lots of things and I usually see - children that's spoiled, they're spoilt today, they won't do anything. It's terrible isn't it? Oh I had a wonderful mother and father, my boys used to do everything for me, the - the - the young
est now is - is fifty - is fifty-five in June, next month, and - and he comes and - he's willing to do all kinds then he won't let me make him even a cup of tea, he makes it. And he always brings something, he never takes anything off me. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your brother died when he was quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, I don't remember the family at all. Only him, and I do remember our Tommy because he was a bonny little boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, we'd to be in bed by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. In summer. And in - in winter - we used to be in bed by just turned {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}half past five{\*\xmlclose}. There was no playing about. Now my boys - they'll tell you, when they were - ever so old, they had to be in for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. There were no - door wouldn't be open if they - if they were - out after that. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}Nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
, were very strict, and he learnt all this off my parents. Yes. I - oh yes, he used to - wish they were here, many a time before he died. And - and - and they used to - used to h
ave to come in and I had to be in. There was no - roaming the streets, there was nothing to roam the streets for. Although Can - Candy Street they used to call it the - you know - called it what there used to be our par - parade up and down Candy Street t
h
en there used to be. And then that was all boards you know. I - I were here when - all Candy Street there were - the Old Volunteers, Abe Brayshaw kept the Old Volunteer, well he were me mother's cousin, Abe Brayshaw, and they kept the Volunteers Arms, and
 
then there was the Cavendish but it was only a little old fashioned pub. And then they built that new one you know, when Manningham's had it, I used to visit Manningham's 'cos the girls and - I - I used to play a lot with them you know. And Smiths - cap p
r
oprietors, they used to have the - where the - picture house is you know, well I used to play with them you see, 'cos - went to school with them and Eva Day you know. At - confectioner's shop. Well the - the sons have it now, but she were a Day before she
 were married you know. But you always took their name didn't they, she was - took the name. Yes, Mrs Hollingsworth. Oh yes. She used to think the world of me, I used to work there you know. Oh yes, I worked there when I lived at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mollit Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. My husband w
ere ill, I used to go at - half past seven in the morning, I had fifteen pounds to put - and I were in the kitchen, I used to do all the cooking. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother always put you to bed when you were a little girl, or did sometimes your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh - no, me mother always - my - my - my father - didn't - put me to - bed at all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How old would you be when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh I'd be about - twelve - eleven to twelve, well - I used to go to bed, I had to go to bed
, they used to - undress myself and - you know, go to byd and undress myself, get into bed, nothing to bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You didn't share your bedroom or bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your parents slept in one room and you slept in the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. Me in the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
We - me mother used to always put the bath in the - in the - kitchen, and it were - you know, it was one of them bigger zinc baths then, in that house, but of course when we lived at Morning Stre
et we had a bath. And - and then you know just be - just afore - about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You were telling me that your mother used to put the bath in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And you used to bath in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 In a big zinc bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well they used to do in them days didn't they. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How often would you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh every week, sometimes twice a week. Yes, I do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was there a special night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well we - it used to be Saturday nights, Friday night and Saturday night you know we - just - depends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about clean clothes, how often would you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh every week. Sometimes - oftener you know, knickers and that. Them bloomers, we used to wear bloomers then. And wool stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where did the family have their meals when you were at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Arcourt Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? Did you have them in the kitchen or in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes, well it - we had them in the house you know, then the - call it dining room and the little kitchen was where you had your washing up and your sink and that you know. But - we used to have it in - the house you know. Where the oven were and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room? You didn't really have another room did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Not there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 In the kitchen, we'd - oven you know. Ordinary oven, beautiful oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was it a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. One of them with a steel top you know. A lovely - oh yes, we did with coke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you had a range but not a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What time would you have breakfast when you were living with your parents and you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When we - oh - we used to get - I used to have to get up at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 45}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}quarter to eight{\*\xmlclose} and - have me breakfast. I had to have a - sometimes I used to have a - a right g
ood - you know, just sponge down, and then breakfast used to be on the table ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother would make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, everything ready for me, on a tray. And there'd be - ham and eggs. Oh yes, and - and - marmalade in a little dish. You know, to h
ave after. Oh yes, I - and I brought my eldest boy up like that you know 'cos he used to travel about with his boss and he used to go - and stay at - Scotland you know, when they were buying and selling wool, and then he used to go on tour with him to Wal
e
s. Used to drive him, oh yes, got on with a - a Taffy, well they used to call him Taffy and - and - he - he came to our house, he'd never seen snow. Couldn't understand a word he said but - our Alfred could you know. And he used to - when we were talking 
to him sometime - he'd get his little book out, he'd say, wait 'til I get me little book. Yes, to see what it meant. Very nice boy, he would have liked to stop forever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you had breakfast would your mother or father have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh me father used to be off to business you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would he take sandwiches for his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he'd have breakfast before he left. Yes, me mother used to get up - she used to get up at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}five o'clock{\*\xmlclose} every morning and - my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you have anything different for breakfast on say Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 On Sunday. No, we used to just have bacon or ham. Just depend, yes. And sometimes sausage with it you know. We used to have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal, did you used to come home from school for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, I never went out to dinner, or went for meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would your mother and father have the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, me mother would and me father, we - my mother used to make a lovely dinner for us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your father used to come home from work for it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes. I remember we used to have - Thursday was liver and onions and dumplings, all - done in the oven, it was lovely you know. She used to make everything so nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What other sort of meal would you have at dinnertime? What else would she make for a dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well we'd have - perhaps a pie one day, you know, potato pie. And another day we'd have - chops or - you know, we'd always varied you know. And then a roast, sometime it'd be lamb. Sometime it'd be si
rloin you know, or - different joints, but she used to cook it so beautifully different ways, well I - I did, my husband had never been used to living like me you know. And - he used to say - well - I - I never - never knew anybody that could do things, I
 said, I was taught. I said, my mother didn't spoil me - that I was helpless when I was married. I could bake or do anything when I were married and I wish I could bake here now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you have a pudding to finish off with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh used to always have
 a pudding, I - we had a sago pudding or - a - a rice pudding or - jam roll, you know, and - they was made like, they wasn't - out of tins or anything like that, your mother was - they was - homemade, they were beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you have anything special on a Sunday for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well sometime we'd have different joint and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 It would always be a joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We always had a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}
 pudding made, my father loved Yorkshire pudding, I did. My mother as well, but remember they used to always have after - treacle on - treacle on it instead of gravy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Have it as a sort of sweet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. Oh she used to have a lot of treacle on her pudding. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about tea, would you all in for tea, would your father be back in time to have tea with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes, and mother used to make all her confectionery, she used to make - meat pies, it were like pasty shape, you know, and - and - we used to have cakes, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Madeira{\*\xmlclose}
 loaf and - coconut came and - and seed cake, she used to make everything, it was
 beautiful, and tarts and custard. But you - they can't make stuff like that now, well it isn't like it because - well I make it meself, I bake that stuff, you know. I - I - I like the best of everything, I like it good because - I mean you get the nouris
hment. You don't what you buy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So at teatime it sounds as if you would have something like pasties and cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh and brown cake and - I live on brown bread. Do now, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You'd have bread and butter and jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. Butter as well, we neve
r had margarine. My husband and my children never had margarine. My sister-in-law used to give them - you know, margarine, and she said, they don't get best butter here, they have margarine. I said, my children gets what I get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 On a Sunday would you have anything special for Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Sometime we'd have a - you know, in summertime we'd have something nice. A salad or anything like that you know, boiled ham, and it were - wasn't out - that wasn't out of a - we used to boil the ham ourself. 'Cos you - yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother or father - your mother baked her own bread didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh yes, she baked every - me and all up to being - I couldn't bake. Having a - do to get the yeast and I baked, oh my husband wouldn't eat - he'd never had a 
bit of homemade bread while he married me and then he wouldn't have no bought bread, we daren't bring it in the house. Well I never bought bread you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she make her own jam, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh sometimes, yes, apricot and I'll tell you what we
 used to have sometimes special I often think about this. I - on - on some Saturday she'd - get a vegetable marrow. And me father'd have some of his - upper ten I called them, you know, friends, and she'd stuff this marrow, and roast it in the oven. Oh it
 
used to be delicious. I often think about it you know, I often - wished I'd have - done that you know, see what she did, yes, because it were lovely and - and she used to make - marrow jam and that used to be nice. Take all the skin off, you know, and cut
 the middle out, and do something with it and it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Marrow and ginger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes, yes, and ginger, she used to - leave it overnight, steeping the mar - marrow when it was - ready to put under pressure. Oh yes, she - she would do all kinds of you know an
d chickens and - game, 'cos she were used to game and that you know, and she knew how to cook anything. She was lovely cook. And - of course she - she taught me and she used to say well you'll have to do this sometime yourself, you know. And - you don't w
a
nt to be married, a man won't want a - a woman that can't do anything for him, you know, well they do marry, they can't do a thing can they. Well you see, and - and my boys, although they're boys - I used to learn them, to do and do you know, my eldest bo
y
 now has to bake for his wife, she is - nearly - crippled with arthritis and she's been nearly dead but she used to smoke and she - she used to smoke that many cigarettes she used to want nothing to eat. And they're - caretakers at - Congregation church i
n
 Bingley, but she's supposed to do the work but my - son goes home from the office at half past four, and he does all the work, even the washing and does his shirts up, and - and - does all the cooking. And does all the work for her in the church, but he 
-
 you know, he had a bad heart, he - he was demobbed out the Army, he collapsed with a ulcer, and they daren't operate on him. Now he's on a diet, and he - he's gone that thin - that thin there, and - and - and do you know, he - we saw him and they thought
 he were going to die, we didn't know where he were, we thought he was killed and - they were both out - me youngest boy were there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she ever bottle her own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she ever bottle her own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh yes, my mother used to bottle carrots - people laugh at me. She used to pickle 'em. Yes, pickle carrots - they used to be lovely, sliced you know. And she used to pickle them like beetroot. And she used to - boil beetroot and - make beetroot wine. 
Oh yes, she did all that and - elderberry wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, she made pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And she made all sorts of wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she ever make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, she believed in herbs 
you know. She's got them and brewed them and - you know, and I gave my husband a - a - herbs for his - and - and barley. She used to believe in barley water you know. And he - I made it, my husband had \{BLANK\}
 disease you know and - they sent him out to Vi
ctory Hospital incurable - when my youngest boy were two year old. Oldest boy. And he - he said - they never knew a man to - have it so bad, and do you know I gave him - barley water every day, I gave him it and - of course especially - I keep doing it yo
u
 see, I put a handful - into a pint of water and I boiled it. And then - and - then I cleaned that water off and then I put another pint of water on top of that barley, and mulled it again, 'cos it looks that dirty you know, first lot so - the other looks
 
pucey, and then - he - he wanted milk and that used to make him drink that instead of having any other drink you see. And - we met Doctor Hepplethwaite - he were his doctor - you know, he used to be where the library is, he was a nice Scots doctor, and we
 was going up Cavendish Street during the first world war, you know, and there were - we were having a picture, 'cos - \{BLANK\}
 disease you know, he's showing it, and he were coming down, he were here, he were - illustrating it you see, and he - he was comin
g down King Street, I didn't know he'd come home, 'cos he were in the war all the time you know, he went to war, and he were coming down and he - he walked - first one side of street and then t'other you know, and - I - I didn't stop him or that but he co
m
e right up and he said it's never Allan Moody is it? I said, yes. He said, what you been giving him? And - I said, nothing doctor, only barley water. He said, he ought to have been dear years since. So you can tell how ill he was. So, he says, well, he sa
ys, he's wonderful. And then he died didn't he, doctor Hepplethwaite and - his wife were a beautiful woman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother ever brew any beer for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, me father wasn't a drinker and my mother wasn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
They did in the north I think, I think me mother - I've heard me - me mother said - that they lived in - they went to live in Scotland in - Inverness on a little thatched farm, and they said - she used to
 pow - plough - I've heard me auntie - Margaret saying, and me Aunt Lizzie, saying - that she used to plough the - the - the ground like a man, and she had two pigs and she used to kill her own pigs and make black pudding and such as that, you see them we
re them days but - I were only quite - I don't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 That's what your aunties told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But when they were living in Keighley they couldn't grow their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would they buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, they bought them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother's parents had this game stall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Game and fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, they didn't sell vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about tinned or dried vegetables or fruit, did you have any of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh me mother used to
 - cook her own pears, she used to - boil her own pears and that you know and these hard pears, she used to get them and - and - such as that and she'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You don't remember her buying tinned or dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I never remember a tin, only once a ti
n came - I knew she used to buy Hohn West salmon. And they used to be tall tins then, you could - and she once - she used to buy it for Sunday tea sometimes - and one day she - opened - one Sunday me dad did - and when he turned it out he - he got a - a l
o
ng bone and he always said it was somebody's finger. And he would never let my mother buy salmon no more. He says, somebody's got their finger off and it had been cooked with the salmon and - you know, I - he - he could tell by the - the shine of the thin
g what it was like you see. So - oh he wouldn't have - no - don't bring me any more tinned salmon. So - that's what he always shied against tinned stuff at all. And I don't eat a lot of tinned stuff. I don't, because I don't - well it's no good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 With y
our mother's parents having this stall where they sold game and fish and things did she got a lot from there? Would they let her have the odd bird?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, she - she paid for everything she got. Oh no, nothing for nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She had to pay for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. Well that isn't business. You - the - the - the profit's going when they're giving - giving it away, I understand that you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father ever keep any hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. When - when he was in the north he used t
o have pigeons, I - I remember him - used to have these pigeons he sent off you know, to fly off, with messages. Of course they do in the north of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} don't they. They're right pigeon fanciers you know, nearly all have pigeons, miners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many times a week would you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh we had it nearly every day. There'd be Monday but - that'd be cold meat from Sunday. Every other day we'd have - our warm dinners. We always had a warm - d
inner. Yes, that's what doctor said, he said, if I hadn't have been well kept - I wouldn't have been here. You see I was able to fight it, although I have a bad heart, I - I sometime now I have these attacks but - yes. I - I - I didn't feel so well this m
orning, I jumped out of bed and - since I had me accident you know me eyes - and I - I - I can't hardly see when I get out of bed you know. I can't hardly open me eyes, and - I was - I jumped out of bed this morning about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 15}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}quarter past six{\*\xmlclose} 'cos I generally get up meself for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}half past five{\*\xmlclose}. Because I don't sleep much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you ever get some extra meat such as a rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes - we used to have rabbit pie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But did you ever know anyone who did any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And would get you free rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. I never remember anything free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You were never short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, but I have and I've had - I've done without to let my children have enough. Yes, oh yes, I have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But your mother always had enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
My mother were always - always - had your meal and - and - you know, there was always - always bought in for the week, that's what I do. I always g
et in my - my groceries - to lessen the week, a loaf lasts me a week. I'm a poor eater. I can get me breakfast and have a - slice of bread, brown bread with treacle on, but best butter you know. And - but it isn't tasting like butter now at all. None of i
t does does it, oh it isn't - same. And - I - I can go all day then without anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you say that your father used to have more at mealtimes, would he have a big appetite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he - father could eat - very well you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So he would have more than you or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well - I think - oh no, me mother used to like - she liked anything. I - I were a - what you call - me mother used to call me a picker. But if I left anything, I didn't want it, I had to eat the next meal. There was no waste. And that's the proper way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You've already told me that your father disapproved of talking at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you were never allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, never allowed to read a Sunday paper when I was a girl. I don't read 'em now, them - papers - and there's nothing in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well we - we really did you know, that's proper way. But - but if we didn't like it me mot
her - if I didn't like it she never made you eat anything you - you - didn't like. But - you know - and - she first - if she bought anything - and - and cooked it and that and - when I say, well I don't like that, you know - well she wouldn't give me any 
of that. It was all right, as long as I didn't get it on me plate. And leave it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If you left anything uneaten on your plate you got it at the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. I had it to eat. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the s
alt, could you ask one of your parents to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well - it was always put there, in the middle of the table, if I - and we could reach it, you see, there was only three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes, if I could eat it. But - if you - they knew you - couldn't - it was getting - going to be wasted they wouldn't give you it. But I always got me way, me mother used to say there's some goes in at the mouth. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
I was supposed to have me spoon, me knife and fork and - everything was set out in perfect order. And we knew which knife and fork to use and
 - you know, and - and spoon, everything. Oh yes, we - we was supposed to be, you know - we were suppose to lady - be lady like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well, you - if yo
u wanted to leave - you wanted to go to the toilet perhaps or something, you'd ask, may I please leave the table? And my boys do that today. And my - my - daughter - daughter-in-law, she - she plays humbly 'cos one day my granddaughter said - she - she wa
n
ted to get up from the table and - they'd finished but they hadn't got up and she says, may I please leave the table. And she clouted her across the face. And I said, what's that for? I lived with them you know. Yes. And I got in - that's why I had this f
u
rniture, I left mine with them. But our Edward had bought the furniture you know, she's second wife, and his - oldest daughter's to his first wife but - he divorced her because she had a man, she'd twins and - when the war was on, and it were Mr Milyneaux
 the Victory's commanding officer, it nearly killed my son - 'cos he never bothered with girls and she were the only one - he married, she used to work at \endash 
 Rustless, and anyway - he divorced her and - he said he - he could have forgiven her - but he said h
aving children and - and he said I went away with my work half done. And he said - but she was never a Christian mother. He said, but if ever you see her, he said, don't walk over the other side of the way. But have a smile for her and feel sorry for her 
- from the bottom of your heart. That's his way. That's my way. I don't hate anyone. And if they hurt me - I just leave them alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you used to have your meals with your mother and father would you all sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, oh yes, we always sat down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you always have the same places round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How was the meal served, did your mother serve it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, mother served it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she have a tureen in the middle and serve it from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She didn't put it on the plates and give it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh no, she used to serve it from the tureen - tureen with potatoes in, and - we used to have the gravy, meat on a plate and me dad used to carve the meat you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well we used to get - pudding first, Yorkshire pudding, if we had {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose} pudding.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But I mean in the family, did she serve your father first or were you served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes-, she used to serve me first sometime and me dad, and then she'd serve herself last see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was your mother an easy person to talk to would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she was a lovely talker, you ought to have heard my mother. People used to say - used to c
ome and ask her the time just to get her to talk. Oh she were right refined. I were when I got married you know. But everything's changed, I - but when I go and I talk to people - you know, different, I can talk to them. I know how to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would she say she was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh she was - understanding, yes. I could ask her a question - and she would understand and she would advise me. Then me father were like that, he was another - he was very understanding, really more - than me mo
ther. You know. 'Cos if I broke a plate or anything - you know, me mother'd come to give me a smack and he'd stop her. He'd say, you can't mend a plate by - smacking her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did she show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh - she loved me did my mother. She loved 
my children. She did live to see my youngest boy seventeen year old you know. And - and she loved them - well, my youngest boy used to never be away from her. He used to love her. She was - oh, she were as good as gold, and I know my daughter-in-law used 
t
o say - oh your mother is a nice - person, she said, I love to go, she said, because, she said, she talks so nice and she - she's so understanding and she advises you, you know, she'd tell you in such a nice way, not like a - some mothers you know they sh
o
ut and they rave, it's awful isn't it. That isn't the way to bring children up I - I love my children and I never had to beat them, and they never do and my - you know my old - my - youngest - son's - father-in-law, he says to my - eldest son, my eldest s
o
n but he - he's seven year and three month older than Edward, and he says - you never hear your Edward - giving back chat to his mother, to our Alfred said, we've no desire to back chat my mother. Said, my mother's worked hard for us, he said, he said, sh
e
's been good to us, we'll never repay for what she done for us. And it's lovely when they say that isn't it. You know, al - although he said it - he - I - I - you know, my heart it - it fair - went out to 'em you know, because they know I'm - I have worke
d and I loved my children and I love me grandchildren.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you say that if you had any worries you could share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, my mother shared - my oldest boy shared my worries. My youngest boy doesn't know all this you know. H
e didn't know - I had a lot I wouldn't like the world to know about, well you can't, it's a private affair but - you see my life was a life of misery - after - about three month - after I were married - everything seemed to go wrong. You know, he used to 
g
o out on his own and he'd drink and he - he - he - he could drink liquor out of a bottle neck. And never be drunk. But he'd be like this here next morning. He hadn't - he was a lovely musician, he could play anything. Beautiful musician, he used to - we u
sed to have a piano and he used to play - play lovely - songs you know, sentimental songs, but - otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you were quite young -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 A girl, you were able to confide to your mother any worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh I used to have to tell - I use
d to take all to me father and mother, used to tell them if I - if I thought I'd done anything I shouldn't have done - at school. I'd go tell them, mother and father, yes, you know, I could - I could trust them not to beat me and know - know - they won't 
- slap me like you know. Mother said, no, you've told the truth and now don't do it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was your father an easy person to talk to as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, I could - I could talk to me dad better than me mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was he affectionate, did he show affection?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Very. He loved me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 They weren't afraid to show their affection for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, they thought the world of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If you had any worries could you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, I could, yes. Me father understood these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh I had to be obedient. I had to be - I had - to - be very - I hadn't to be cheeky or anything like that and was brought up - to be a - I was brought up in a proper wa
y - from being ever so young, I had to speak when anyone else was speaking, or they were speaking, I had to be there - and just listen. You see. And then - and if - I wanted to ask anything - I had to - wait while they was done talking and then I used to 
ask them. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh, now - that - that - if - if anyone hit - hit me you know and they come and - I'd hit them back they'd come and tell me dad - I - I know one woman brought he
r daughter back, anyway - well me father - she - she told me father, he said, well, she's big enough to - stick up for herself, he said, and my daughter is going to - hit back, she isn't going to - stand still. Well there were nobody would would they. But
 
- he said, but he - he wouldn't - he didn't like me to be like that - and he wasn't viol - violent or that. Scared to death when - violence or anything you know I think it's horrible and - these poor little children abroad it makes me sick when I - you kn
ow, yes, well I could cry because - they're all - God's children and I mean - they're all human, you - aren't they. There is bad - as I say, coloured people and there's bad - British people, white people. We have a lot of - Hitlers here - in the world.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What kind of a person do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well, they brought me up and they - they knew some day that I'd be left - I never thought so, and they said that - well when you live your own life - you've been taught, 
and it always pays to be honest, and trustworthy, and do your work, and always remember that if you don't do your work - your boss, your employer, isn't going to get the money that he's entitled to, and therefore he can't be paying you wages, 'cos - you a
r
en't doing the work he's set to do, and it - it - I was all brought up to - to respect people older than meself, and you know, and not to be - knowing more than them, 'cos nobody knows - more than anybody, they're all - we're all - in a school lot of time
 aren't we.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well - they - they didn't say money was important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What did you think you ought to consider as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well - they - they said like th
at - I'd to do right and and right would be come on me and - that I had to make - if I had nothing to make me what I had do, never take anything that didn't belong me, and - if I could help anyone in life - I had to help them, it didn't matter whether the
y were - lived in a mansion or they lived in - the slums. He said it - there's a lot of - decent people he said - and never look down on anybody even - a man or a woman - if they aren't as nice dressed as you, well don't - clothes don't make the person.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh we never swore. Oh my boys never swear. But they - they tell me - another chap come here and - I said - even my - my youngest son, one of the boy - young mean he said to me, he's a foreigner, he's Italian, he sai
d, oh he's a good boss, you know, he's a foreman, and he says - yet he never - hear - hear him swear nor nothing he said, and there were a chap, he were helping a - an old man to - to - put some - you know, these here - ovens and what they'd doing, enamel
l
ing, on the rack and one of the men - big Irish man he said - what do you help them for he said, you should come watching 'em? He said, I'm here to do - my work as well as you, he said. He said, and I help him, he said, because I'll be old some day. And -
 and the other chap said, when you going to learn to swear when you hear us swearing but he said I never hear you. You see, that - that's how they've been brought up. I never swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh well if I - if I needed a - smacking I'd get it off me mother, me father never beat me. But I - I'd only had one - off me mother, but - it wasn't for nothing real
ly wrong but - I had to - I had to - do as they were brought up, I had to be a - obedient and I had to be as they could take me anywhere. You see. Because if you don't and take your children anywhere and they - they carry on, because some do you know, eve
n my grandchildren you know. That - me grand - daughter's husband comes, he's an inspector, police inspector you know well sergeant in the platoon and then - he got moved to - he'd passed - two years since for inspector. Oh aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When your mother used to smack you was it very rarely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I - I - I only remember once I was smacked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I don't know, I - I - I'd - gone out and stopped out or something. I know I - she did smack me. Oh she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How did you feel afterwards? What did you feel about her smacking you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well, you see, I - with always being taught - you know, seeing other children - I thought well I deserve it, you see. I always - 'cos you see I'd been brought up to realize and understand - that I - I'd been naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your father never did smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, they were both alike. They both ar
e the same, my father and mother - used to sit and plan their life. They was a real happy couple. You know, it was awful, I used to think about this here you know, that my father - came to see me every week. I had to meet him. And then he came to see my m
o
ther you see. And - he - he said - well I - I think I shall make up with your mother, 'cos I - I were a woman then you know, and my oldest boy were eighteen then, and - and he said - 'cos we'd never - and you know he always - when she was there if he came
 and she was there, he - he'd just talk to her and he'd done before. He said nobody'd every take her place. And he said no one was fit to tie her shoe string. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But he wouldn't go back to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He couldn't get over that, he - he said she spoile
d my life. Well I said these things has to be. And the test in life and I think - we have to experience these things to learn a lot. But - what my husband, he - he wasn't - he didn't curse a lot but his sister did you know, they wasn't my kind - they wasn
'
t brought up like me but I used to - they used to call me the saint, you can tell what they used to think about me, if they saw me coming a woman told me, well Mrs Trotter - she went to America and she - she were in Clara's house and I were going across t
o her sister, she lived in Cook Street, and - she says, oh - oh and I'll be getting a lot of trouble, here's the saint coming. You see? But her never said anything to her about it, I thought well - well ignore 'em see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you had a birthday when you were a little girl would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
I don't think so, not if they love the children. I know my mother used to make a party and then I used to have - about twelve companions come you know. Oh - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would there be any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would there be any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. And there'd be a little present for all them that come. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you have something special to eat at the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh well used to make all sorts of trifle and jellies and all - k
ind of fruit and sweets you know, although I - I never - was never encouraged to have a lot of sweets. But - I - I don't - like a lot of sweets now. I'll have a chocolate now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But this was something special she made for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Can you remember anything you did with your parents together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well, yes - you'd have - I were born on Christmas Day but they didn't christen me - on the twenty-seventh. And do you know - I know - one time - a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you'd have your birthday party on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes. Yes. And a lady once said to me she say - oh she says to mother she said well - well she was a lovely Christmas box. You know, she think there was nothing like me. She - I - I was - I used to be nice looking an
d - and she said she was dear little gift, you know, a real Christmas box. Dear little gift. But she - you know - she was ideal mother, and ideal father. And they always told me now then - you know - you don't perhaps always agree with one another, and th
e
y used to say, you want to be like - your - your mother and - and me, and - if you don't agree, let - let them - see let my husband, I had to let my husband think what he thought and think what I thought myself. Don't argue. Says, that cause a - a great d
e
al - of - of emotion, and it causes unhappiness. He said, you - you should think and plan your money, that's what my husband done, thought he didn't give me no money, and he used to have only nine and six and then sometime I - well I'd be on - on - on me 
p
iece work you know. But we - that's all we got. Twelve shilling were the highest wage then you know. And - and I used to - come home on Friday, and I'd - hand me money, and I'd only that you see and I'd got me money to pay out, and then I had to - then - 
if there were anything left it were mine, if there wasn't well - to do the best I could. I've had to go without many a meal now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 To let your children have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And bring my husband - help them and keep them going. I - I've had a slice of bread in
 me hand and they've had a lovely dinner I've cooked night before, I used to - do the potatoes, put them in - in a pan, wash 'em and put them in a pan and I used to leave my husband, he - he - he used to sit in a chair, you know, couldn't lay down in bed,
 
oh no, then when he died he choked and it - oh - blood nearly reached the ceiling, it were terrible. And - and he - I used to say to him, now - you can manage - if you can, to put a light to the potatoes. And I used to cook the meat at night, and he used 
to go home and bake a stone and a half of bread. Yes, I did, anybody'll tell you that that's living, there's lots living that did know, and I used to run home - from - for - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Goldman Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} right up to Lanes Road right up to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Belgrave Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and I used to se
rve the meals for them. My hus - my oldest son sometimes made - he - he'd - you know - 'cos he - he - he'd got married when he were - twenty-five, my youngest boy did, and they hadn't got married, the - the oldest boy married his - childhood sweetheart, s
o
 did - the - me young son. Well - they - they - I used to run home and - he'd have it all ready, but I'd mash the potatoes and soon get them onto the plates, and I know the doctor's come in to him many a time and he's looked and he's said to the, well if 
you get that on your chests you'll not all anything, you know. And - and my husband said, look, that's what she does. Slice of bre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10816464\charrsid5456321 ad in her hand. S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 lice of buttered bread. And doctor used to well - it'll do more good than anything. 'Cos it were good best but
ter but - he - he - he said many a time, if she hadn't - if you hadn't had - a good bringing up, you couldn't have carried on. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Christmas Day was your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you do anything of a sort of Christmas nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you sing carols or would there be Christmas presents as well as birthday presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh yes, oh yes, always a Christmas present you know - there was always something - that I never knew about it'd be there on the table. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you sing carols together, the three of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you sing carols together, the three of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Carols.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, we had to - yes, we had done many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Me father used to play a cornet. Yes.
