and when we got there me grandma came out there and she said - are you going down home da? And - he never spoke. And - he were right god living man, he - quiet man, but he'd been poorly with - gall stones, and the - he wouldn't have operation, said God ne
v
er made us to be cut up, he didn't believe in it, and they passed to his liver, and he'd walked down the street dead. He'd be - just walk to the top to have a bit of fresh air, and then he was walking back. And he - she say, are you going down home now da
?
 And - and - he never spoke, and she touched him you know on the shoulder, and he fell on his hands and nose - knees, and when she tried to get him up he rolled over onto the back on the pavement, but they didn't touch him you know, but he used to have - 
