\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We used to go every year - the last week in August and the first week in September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You'd just go for the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We'd go - oh well there was - they didn't go off for months like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where would you go to, would it vary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We all - yes, we'd - very and - we'd get down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 'Cos we had relations in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and - Shepherds Bush, and we'
d get down there and - we'd spend a week there. I - I've been to Southend. South - Southend, Westmor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10816464\charrsid5456321 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
land from here. It's lovely there and all. Oh yes, we - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you went to a variety of places for you holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. And it was a lot warmer
 down south and my mother used to love to go south because she said it was warmer in winter than what it was in - in - these - country you know. The - up here. Because - well it's south there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 We were just talking about your holidays that you used to go on with your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you were on holiday what sort of thing would you do during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well we - we - we - I never used to leave me parents you know, we used to go - on the - theatre, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10816464\charrsid5456321 know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 , or that, but - and - we'd go
 and sit on the front you know get the fresh air, and - where we went if there was a park we'd get there. But otherwise if we didn't - we didn't spend a lot of money. No, you know, you - you don't - yes, quiet holiday 'cos I mean it's no good going on hol
iday really, well we thought so - you go for a rest, not for to be chasing about 'cos some of them - they're worse when they come back than what they are when they went. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Could you tell - me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Saturday? We
ll - we - in me childhood you mean? Oh - Saturdays were like any other day really. And mother'd - perhaps - we'd go up the town and sometimes go into Devonshire Park, we'd go in - we used to Long Park, but otherwise it - and we - we'd walk up to Bromkey. 
Oh we used to walk up there, used to walk up there many a time, we've gone up and - and gone up Parry's Lane and we've walked right round and come down where, you know, Bell Horse Lane, right down into Howarth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well Sunday - was a - a - I used to spend in church, going to church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have any different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. I never wore me Sunday clothes through the week. I always had to have them on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you say that your parents thought it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
We used to - we - in - me father were right good living you know and he - he used to - me mother and him went to church but we never played anything on a Sunday, we kept it reverent. Because it's God's Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But she would work on a Sunday but you weren't allowed to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would your mother make the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 That's all. Oh - oh she'd make me - if you want anything in between or anything li
ke that, get it yourself. She wouldn't entertain it, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh my father and mother were - they used to go to - my mother were parish church and me father were Wesleyan Methodist. Oh they used t
o go both him and her to chapel did me father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So they both went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes. When she married me dad you know used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How often would they go, would it be every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh every Sunday, they never missed. Every Sunday night. Night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you attend as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I've always been brought up - as I tell you, I'm - I'm God fearing, I believe in God and I pray to God every night and every morning.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you used to go with your parents to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Y
es, I used to have to - I had to go. Yes, Sunday school at afternoon, and Sun - and the morning I had to go to Sunday school and all, there were no getting away from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you went three times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Three times a day. And then - we'd have different 
clothes on every time we went, we used to always have three changes. Yes, and everything were made, you know, of course they were different to what they are today, they don't care about their children at all some of them. They don't care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, they used to go from the schools, I used to go with my - my grand daughter from up on - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Sale{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But when you were a little girl were there Sunday school outings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, we used to go all over
 the - we used to go - all over you know, we used to go and we used to walk to a place called Ferry Hill, you know, they're all country roads, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You'd go walks would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, and to Trimden Colliery, we'd walk to Trimden Colliery, me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10816464\charrsid5456321  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 auntie - Auntie Win, there were no road, there was no - there was no buses up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But were there Sunday school trips out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, we used to go and we used to - you know, have little picnics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You'd take a picnic with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, all of us, we all took something and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were there any other social activities organised by the chapel that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have any concerts or dances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I remember - we had - we've had teas but - I don't remember - we've had concerts like they have now you know but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would you be in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, 'cos - we'd be in them and we'd be - we'd get - Babies in the Wood and Cinderella you know and - all kinds of the old fables.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 The chapel would put these on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh 
no, they'd be on the - they'd be on the little - they'd have a little stage and platform you know. Oh we used to have it like - well we used to have it on the floor you know, and have a space - entertained where they used to have the little rostrum you kn
ow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you belong to the choir at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did the chapel run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I don't remember that. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you used to say grace at meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 All of us, me father, yes, always say - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were you taught to say prayers at night before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, we was taught to thank God for what we'd received through the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you ever have family prayers when all three of you would pray together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
No, I don't remember but - me - me father used to always say - used to always pray they prayed and all, and I used - he used to always say well - he used to read the Bible to us at Sunday, ge
t the Bible and - yes, and used to say God asks us to pray you know. That people want some answer then, but it's impossible, we come under God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you know what his political views were at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well, me father was a Conservative, I do know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Why do you think he held these views would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Why do you think he held these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well he - he said that the - you get - he said, I - I don't delve into politics
, he said, and therefore he said, I keep out of it. He said, because it makes a lot of trouble for you and it makes trouble for other people. He - said, but, he said, I - I should think that a man should have his own views and his own ideas, he should wat
ch the goings on, you know, and experience, he said, you learn better by your own experiences.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about your mother, did she have any political ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she - followed me father, as - she all - she - she were a Conservative the same as him, b
ut anyway they changed you know. Oh they changed to Labour. When Mr Lee - you know, they had been changed by Lee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would that be during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, first world war, yes it was. And he was a poor man, he was a working man you know, j
ust office man of some kind. He put up and he had no car nor nothing, but he were a wonderful man, and we got our first rise in - his - what do you call it, what we - you know, before we got - well before I got me pension of course I were sixty, he were h
ere. In me forties you know. But he was a lovely man and - he was for the working man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And he became Mp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes. He died, he were - he were a nice chap. But he - he didn't ride about in no - because he - you know, nothing - like that, he - he was a 
man that was a worker for the working people, and everybody seemed to turn towards him because he got a lot of things done in the short time he was - in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Can you remember your father and mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, they used to vote every - every - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother voted as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Proper - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Women didn't get the vote until 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No they didn't, oh - no, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So as soon as she got the vote she made use of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, oh she made use of it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you know what party they voted for in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would it be Labour by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. There were Liberal and Conservative then, there wasn't no Labour but - they are like Labour was Liberals wasn't the
y, they weren't - the same but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What would he vote for if he voted in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh Conservative. Oh he was a right blueberry. Yes. He was a member of the Conservative club, he was a chairman on the committee, and he - they had property down there,
 where Prince Smith's, by the - where the - that property down there, it all belonged to Prince - Conservative - Club, and of course he was shareholder. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they vote
d differently from their employers. Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, because they - they didn't do that. No. Didn't do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He would be at the gasworks then would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your father was a member of the Conservative Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would that mean that he was a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He was - the committee, was on the committee, was the chairman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember him working for the Conservative party at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I don't remember that you know, but - I know he was a - a real blue berry and we used to have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your mother never worked for the party did she, for the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
No, I don't think so. No - the - the - they - they used to vote and all that and - for the Conservatives, me father used to say you know, they're all for theirselves, not for you poor people. All them men that has all this money, 
he said, been easy got - in their life, and he said, and - they - they're making such promises that they never fulfill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yet he remained a Conservative?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You see there were only the Liberal then, yellow and blue, and then it changed to Labour as 
well you see. But Labour and - and Liberal, they seemed to work on the same methods. They seemed to work for the people. And I think the Labour party is. I do. I - I - I vote Labour, I don't care who knows. I - and - and I - I say that - that the people l
ike Mr Wilson, so does Mr Heath, but they left the Labour in debt before they come out, and they had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10816464\charrsid5456321  to pay all the - all their debt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 s, and get them all straightened up, and - and they were just getting them nice, and I think Wilson was foolish to have that 
election so soon. You see, but I feel here myself you know, that the - the - they'll have a general election, and the Labour'll get back. Well because they did more and it's all right them saying they - they did this, now they're beginning to see their mi
s
take a lot of 'em. And you see they're all voting Labour, the there's more Labour getting in aren't they, and I hope they do because he isn't fit to be a - he isn't fit to be a Minister. I don't think so, I don't know what you think. I mean - it isn't 'co
s
 he's wealthy and all that I don't envy his wealth 'cos I'm - I'm happier than he'll be. But he - he's doing things in a - a - a funny way and trying to get into the Common Market, but do without the Common Market, and there wouldn't be a France and it's 
t
hem that's - put all obstacles in us way, now they're trying to get us in, but they're going to have money out of us, and - and - wanting so much money down aren't they? Eighty thousands, before you can join the Common Market. Then they want you to give u
p with - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}New Zealand{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and - and - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Australia{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. Well we've always - done with them - deal with them, and they deal with us. But he's just destroying it. He's destroying everything, and - it's going to cause war. There'll be a revolution. And - and I'm - they ha
ven't - tried to blow him - they - they've blown Mr Carr, I feel he's been a bit quieter since it. And you know, look how - but they shouldn't do that. But I mean they're doing this aren't they? And that's the people that's supposed to be Conservatives an
d that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When your parents were not doing their work, I know they wouldn't have much spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. Not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How did they spend their spare time if they had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well you know, you - they had to be up for six o'clock in the mo
rning to work - to start to work at six, I did, and work for half past five at night, sometimes we worked while six, we did when the first world war come out, and - and - and - well the - the night was gone. They'd go - some'd go to the theatre or - or th
e Queen's Theatre, we had a lovely theatre, they should have kept it going shouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But you don't remember your parents doing any of these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. I don't remember them ever being people that - sought pleasure on the out side of their - of their life you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So they just went to work and looked after the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
That's right. They looked after their home and - and you could have picked up a pin in my mother's home - it - it was spotless, could have ate off the floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother have any interests outside the home? Other than the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. She was a person that kept herself to herself. And me father was the same. He was very careful who he'd choose you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Do you remember her ever going out to enjoy herself, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I don't. I remember my mother working hard all her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When did your father get home from work in the evening, when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well it'd - it'd - be perhaps - six or half past when he'd get home, you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many evenings a week would be spent at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Every evening. I remember - I never remember my - my - my father going out and - he never went out without me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But he was a chairman at the Conservative Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh well he'd have to go then. He'd go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many nights would that involve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well - sometime it used to be every month and sometime every fortnight, it wasn't every - yes, very rare. Just keep bringing things up you know as cropped up I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So he didn't go out to have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, he - he'd have a - a glass of beer - but he'd have it in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He wouldn't go in a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Or a club to have it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, he said a man - he said he didn't believe in just goin
g and having drink and - keeping a fat landlord. He said, drink's all right to a man, a man deserves a drink that works hard, he said - when they go in and abuse it and - make a - a fool of theirselves, he says, well - they want to leave it alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother ever go to the Conservative club with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, she never went in them places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father ever take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I - I can't remember. I - I remember when we were in Durham going, Durham Big Meeting, what they
 called Durham Big Meeting, they used to have live the galas here you know. 'Course that's going back years ago, yes. And they used to have a - a - you know - a right happy day and - I remember going to them Big Meetings. I remember going, I remember that
 
and - I remember it - I went round with the wheel and I had a big cut on me head and that, I know me Uncle Jack, me father's - well youngest brother but one, and - and he played up because he used to be my favourite uncle, he used to - you knoe, he - he p
layed up with this cyclist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he ever attend the races, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, he liked to go to the races, he - well he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would he have a bet when he was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, have a bet. He once had a lot of money stole off him and all at t
he races, out of his - out of his back pocket. He always said it - cut his pocket right out, he said, always said the train was packed and - when they were going to Ripon and - he - he'd never forget it and he had his wallet there and somebody took it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your mother used to go with him to Ripon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. I've gone to the races with him. Gone to Wetherby and - and I've gone to Saltburn races you know and that at Saltburn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs such as a boot club, or a sick club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. There were - there was no sick clubs them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 A funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, they never bothered over it. Not as I know of, I never knew.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you were little did you used to play with the children next door or neighbours in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You kept to yourselves did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You had no particular friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh I had a friend, one of my cousins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where did you play when they used to come and play with you, would it be in the yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Or in the garden or in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I didn't have to play in - in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
When your cousins came to play with you, or when you went to play with your cousins, would you play in the house or in the street or in the garden or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well we would play in the garden with them, but - we - we'd really - be more in the house than our side you know. But I were never allowed to roam the streets at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were you allowed to get dirty when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh I - I
 did get dirty you know - I don't remember - they didn't like to see you dirty, she was very particular. But - you didn't - well I - I never was a child, don't remember playing in dirt or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What games did you play with your cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh we used to skip and play hopscotch, you know, and shuttlecock and battledore weren't there, but I used to have a whip and top, I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. Me father and mother really, they shi
elded me you know, they didn't want me to - get - 'cos you know some children, they were - allowed to do just what they liked. But my mother didn't want for me to get like that.
\par 
