\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he came for our - I had - I had t
he doctor for 'em both. Had Doctor Hepplethwaite and then he went to - the war you know and - four our - our Edward he - he went to - he - he went in the first world war did Hepplethwaite and he lived by - where the library is now, the children}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 s library, 
and - he delivered me first boy, and he - he asked me mother, he said, what did you let - your daughter marry that man for? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did your husband help at all, during the confinements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. He was miles away, run out and - he never went to work an
d that night 'cos I told him I'd leave him after me baby were born you know. And he went on his bended knees and he said I've never - I'll never go drinking no more, he never went no more. It cured him. And - but - he thought I'd leave him at - when he we
re at work you know, when he was working at Botany.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How soon were you out of bed with the first boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh the first boy - I were about a month in bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And with the second one it was sixteen weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well, I was in bed - a fortnight, 
and after the ninth day - well you see and I'd had the - I'd had that disturbance with me - you know, with - having left it - in me body, and - and - so I had to go to the hospital 'cos you know I were feeling terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 So you were in hospital about sixteen weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, about sixteen week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How did you manage while you were in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh me mother come, me mother come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And she looked after the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh she took the boys, she took both boys, they loved my mother did my chil
dren. She used to always call me youngest boy, even when he got a young man, she used to always say the baby. Where's the baby, why hasn't he been, 'cos he used to call every day to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did any of your relations or neighbours help, other than your mother, or did your mother do everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh - my - me mother did all for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She looked after the children, did she make your husband's meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 She kept - she kept them home, and then she used to bring a cooked meal for my husband, but h
e could cook anything could my husband, anything, he - he could cook yes. Oh he wouldn't pine himself, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he make your meals as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, me mother made gruel and she used to - make things - so that I - there'd be there all night so I could
