\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh yes, I'd rather - I wouldn't - I wouldn't have weaned them because they - I had a terrible
 lot of milk. Yes, when I were working I used to hate it you know, and I - and when I'd get home I'd go round to her that nursed him, she used to be a nurse, she were getting on though, and she used to mind him and that night and day when I were on nights
 you know, and I used to feed him with me breast, and then I used to buy - two pints of milk a day - to give him, you know, rusks or - or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If you needed advice who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well I - I used to ask me mother, I thought well she'd had all them children, sher were - mother - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If the baby was a sleep would you wake him for a feed or would you let him sleep on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh I used to - feed him at certain times and I kept to that routine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 If he cried before the normal time would you feed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What did you do if he didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he was a good eater, and - and he used to - but - with milk but I used to give him rusks as well you see, when
 he were getting - 'cos he was such a big boy. They both were but - oh, you know - it - it were lovely you know, people used to - you know used to see other mothers giving the children bits of bread and this and - well my mother used to say, never give bi
ts to a baby like that never give it anything like that, give it a proper meal. And - and - and then have a certain time to give it it's next meal. A baby will feed - really wants feeding often when it's just getting milk doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How long would you let it go on feeding for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Well I - I'd let it go on for - when it give up itself, I had him - used to belch you know, then I gave up and then I wouldn't give him any more, and he'd go content to sleep, I never knew I had him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How old was he when you first gave him solid food, rusks and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 About twelve month. And then I - it'd be a few mashed potatoes in butter and milk and, you know - gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When did you wean him off breast feeding altogether, how old would he be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He'd be about nine month old. Yes, I gave him rusks and - ordinary milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You gave him a bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, no bottles then, no bottles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When you weaned him was it sudden or gradual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh gradually, I keep - letting him have a drink of milk you know
, and give him rusks and that, I used to let him - have another - get rid of it 'cos - you see me breasts used to get so big you know and hard and sore and - so - and I - I weaned him gently I didn't do no drastic things to get rid of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he seem to mind being weaned, or doing it gradually do you not think he noticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Yes. No, he didn't, he - he got used to - well he never bothered. And - and dummies, and when I see people with - I never gave him a titty, no. No. Well he wouldn't have it 'co
s there were nothing in it you know. His father once had him out and he brought him one and he's still crying, he carried him up - up canal and he threw it on floor you know he never - and - and he - when he comeback he said, he cried. I said, I know he w
ere crying because - he wanted his titty, but - he said, well, he said, I bought him a dummy but he threw it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you think at the time that it did any harm to let a baby cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well I do, I don't think it's wise to let - especially a boy. 'Cos they can rupture theirselves you know, children - boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you punish them when they were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well they were never naughty, I can honestly say I never had to beat my children. I never had to beat them - do you know - people say to 
me you have put your boys on a pedestal. I said, I have - of course they do. My boys never caused me any trouble. And they never brought me any trouble. And they've never given me a back answer in their life and they're men today and they wouldn't back an
swer me now. They appreciate their mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How much did your husband have to do with your children when they were babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he loved them. He loved them. Oh he loved them, he'd take - used to take our Edward out - in - in - in his long clothes you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he ever feed them or bath them or change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, he wouldn't do anything like that, he wouldn't - wouldn't wash up or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Would he play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh he'd play - he'd buy them all kinds - whe
n he'd have a - a win he'd buy 'em all sorts., I - there wasn't only little toys, he'd buy them such as steam engines. Used to be a shop on Skipton road like Johnson's you know, but it were Mitchell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 s, and he used to - and he used to buy 'em these engines 
you put steam in and they'd go - lovely, and they were a lot of money. Used to buy 'em them, because he used to play with them you see. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he ever get them to sleep for you, when they were very tiny I mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I nev - I - I - my husband wouldn't mind me children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He wouldn't look after them for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No, and he used to say to me - what did I marry you for, what did I pay seven an six for? That's what I got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did he ever get up during the night with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no, he'd never go. Do you - that's a thing I never had to do. Never got up with me children, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He would take them out with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, he'd take 'em out and he'd play with them, he'd buy them all kinds of - right expensive - they'd - boxing gloves and 
- and - and - what they call its, you know - exercising things, dumb belles and - these - you know, what they swing in the air, he'd them, clubs and - oh yes, he'd - they'd everything - well he had - they had a room - of their own, playroom, and there'd b
e
 expanding things you know and I used to say they're pulling their arms out. And they - my husband used to go wrestling, he used to go to Hayes, you know, learning to - not wrestle - you know, all - exercises. Yes, weightlifting and that and - and - exerc
ising.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
I want to ask you now how you and your husband managed the housekeeping in the years before 1919. Did you know what your husband earned when he did go to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I never - I never knew I - 'cos he never give me any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 He never gave you any of it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No. I never remember having a - a wage off my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you used to discuss how the money should be spent, I should say your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well right - right away sometime he'd take the money and go out and buy things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 How many rooms were there in the house at Fruit Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Two bedrooms. An attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And a kitchen was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 And a kitchen and a - a kitchen and a house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Was there a cellar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Were there any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Never had no lodgers in me life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You never had any paid help in the house did you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You did your own washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes. Me own baking and all, I used to come home at nig
ht and - do all me own baking, me husband once did bake - about three year before he died, he - he - I went to work and - the - you know, sick visitor come. She come to see me but - and - and she did fight for - she were a young person like you, she worke
d for one of the ministr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
es and she - she said, Mrs Moody, she said, you should be having pension for your husband. And he said, well I don't think so. She said, oh for the work, the - the last nine years, she said, before he died - she said you ought to ha
ve a hundred pound and she tried to get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you used to make or mend the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh aye, oh yes, I can do - well yes, they were never ragged children, I never seen my children - I were right proud of my children, I was poud and all myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did you make the clothes for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I used to make all - when they were little I used to make all their little britches you know and get them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321 jerseys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321  and - I used to have them all awfully nice and - I used to do without meself to make me children nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did they ever have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. No, they didn't. I used to always put a few shilling a week away if it were only two shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Where were the clothes bought when you bought them anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well there were - Burto
ns you know, Burtons, well they'd only just been built them when our Eddie was born, Burtons. Well I used to go there and there used to be little suits in the window and all, I - I remember once when he were - I britches him when he were three in them lit
t
le - print suits they are, and - and then - when I - when he got to be two year old I - I bought - I saw this suit in Burtons and I thought, oh it is nice, it weren't a lot of money but - it were a lot of money them days, so - oh I said, I'll go in and it
 
had a white collar and it were pea green, and oh it was lovely. And it were like a little waistcoat you know, like silver buttons here. Oh it were beautiful. And - and - and I took him with me and I bought him this. And - and he looked right nice. Now his
 
father'd go, if he had a - a win he used to back horses you know, he were a gam - a right gambler, and - he used to win, he were lucky though, and he'd say get the children ready and take 'em down to Leeds and you get ready, and he'd take 'em down Leeds a
nd buy - he'd dress them. Whatever he saw - on a - on a doll in a window, he'd go - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 This would be winnings from horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh it was his horses, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 When would they get new things, would it be once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh - every - they had - e
very year they had two dons. They never went ragged and he always - they didn't have Saturday and Sunday alike. They were made - like other children, they could go out anywhere, I could take them anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 What about shoes, did they get new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 
Oh they were hard on - yes, they got new shoes but they're rather heavy on their feet, but of course you could get a pair of good shoes for twelve and something, or for - for less. Two and eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Did they have to wear clogs for school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Never wore clogs in their life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 They wore shoes all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes, I never wore clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 You just told me that your husband never helped with cleaning or cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Oh no. Oh - oh no, he nev}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7808927\charrsid5456321 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321  -
