five, they used to be a man - selling papers, and he used to - be shouting paper, you couldn't tell what he was shout - shouting, and - and - they used to say, what - what is that man shouting mum? And I'd say - he's - looking for little boys that aren't 
i
n bed. And - and oh an awful lot tell their children. He used to come round, he used to shout, any little boys - boys tonight, any little boys tonight. And they used to go to bed at half past five, and no bother, but they'd be up at six o'clock in the mor
ning.
