\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Well for Sunday dinner, sometime it was a roast of beef, sometimes
, it was a chicken, and - and sometimes it'd be lamb, a leg of mutton, I love leg of mutton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 But you said you used to make an evening meal when you got home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 I'd cook - yes when I were working. But for weekend - when I came home - at -
 at Monday - we'd have the cold meat from Sunday. But - through the week then I used to get - stewing meat. Then - one day - and we'd have dumplings, I'd make them - and - and I mixed them and put them in a bowl and for my husband - just to scoop them int
o
 the - and put them on - twenty minutes, you know - about twelve o'clock and then they'd be all ready when we got home. Oh yes. Oh yes I did - my - my children tell you, they was never made - shift - I call 'em shift meals, they were never shoved with fis
h and chips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5909703 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 They had proper meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3691612 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971545\charrsid5456321 Yes.
